╭─ assistant [MainThread@3047856] ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ THOUGHT                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ I have analyzed the crash report and the provided LLVM IR. The crash occurs in the `simplifycfg` pass. The backtrace points to `llvm::CallBase::paramHasNonNullAttr`, which asserts that │
│ the argument it's checking must be a pointer. The assertion fails because the argument being passed is a vector of pointers (`<2 x ptr>`), not a scalar pointer.                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ This happens inside the `passingValueIsAlwaysUndefined` helper function in `SimplifyCFG.cpp`. This function is called during speculative execution analysis. When it is called           │
│ recursively on a value that has a vector type (in this case, the result of a `getelementptr` with a vector index), it finds its use in a `call` instruction. It then iterates through    │
│ the call's arguments and incorrectly tries to check for the `nonnull` attribute on the vector argument itself by calling `paramHasNonNullAttr`, leading to the assertion failure.        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The fix is to modify `passingValueIsAlwaysUndefined` to correctly handle vector-typed arguments. The `nonnull` attribute is defined for pointers, not vectors. Therefore, when iterating │
│ through the arguments of a call, if an argument is found to be of a vector type, the check for the `nonnull` attribute should be skipped for that argument.                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will use `sed` to insert a check into `llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/SimplifyCFG.cpp`. The check `if (CB->getArgOperand(i)->getType()->isVectorTy()) continue;` will be added inside the   │
│ argument-iterating loop within `passingValueIsAlwaysUndefined`, right after the loop begins. This ensures that vector arguments are skipped before the problematic call to               │
│ `paramHasNonNullAttr`. After applying the fix, I will submit the patch.                                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '/for (unsigned i = 0, e = CB->arg_size(); i != e; ++i)/a \      if (CB->getArgOperand(i)->getType()->isVectorTy()) continue;' llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/SimplifyCFG.cpp &&       │
│ submit-patch                                                                                                                                                                             │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
